OL,3,CCalls for full review of system used
OL,4,Cto warn people of flooding threat
OL,6,F"The intensity and duration of the
OL,7,Frainfall on steep-sided valleys mean
OL,8,Fthat river levels rise incredibly
OL,9,Fquickly. The River Taff rose 300mm
OL,10,Fevery 15 minutes at the height of the
OL,11,Frainfall. The limited period between a
OL,12,Fflood warning being issued and impacts
OL,13,Fbeing experienced underlines the rapid
OL,14,Fresponse of the Taff to the intense
OL,15,Frainfall.Our warnings are issued when
OL,16,Fflooding is expected to make sure
OL,17,Fpeople have advanced warning and are
OL,18,Fprepared, but we also have to strike a
OL,19,Fcareful balance between issuing
OL,20,Fwarnings and giving communities false
OL,21,Falarms."
